sion (distilling deep networks into executable code trees), and explainable AI (generating human-readable justifications for black-box predictions). We validate AFGI on synthetic benchmarks with mixed decomposition modes, demonstrate its superiority over pure symbolic regression and RUD variants on the Feynman Database, and show its ability to extract modular policies from reinforcement learning agents. By unifying ideas from grammatical inference, program synthesis, and interpretability, AFGI moves beyond static decomposition toward a dynamic, adaptive understanding of functional intelligence.",
